@startuml MatchMonitorClassification_SP_Completed
title CTS_DC_CustClassification_MatchMonitor_Completed - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #FFE0B2
skinparam activityBorderColor #F57C00
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D

start
:SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_MatchMonitor_Completed**;
note right
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsServiceAdmin
  **Purpose**: Mark match and tickets as processed
  **Called by**: ClassifyMatchMonitor Job (after classification)
  **Transaction**: Auto-commit or explicit transaction
end note

partition "Input Parameters" {
  :Receive Parameters;
  note right
    **@ip_MatchID** (INT)
    - Match that was just processed
    - Must be valid MatchID
    - Cannot be NULL
    
    **@ip_MMDetailsIDList** (VARCHAR/TEXT)
    - Comma-separated fraud ticket IDs
    - Example: "12345,67890,11111"
    - Can be empty if no fraud detected
  end note
}

partition "Parse Ticket ID List" {
  if (@ip_MMDetailsIDList IS NOT NULL AND @ip_MMDetailsIDList != ''?) then (yes)
    :Create Temp Table;
    note right
      **Temp Table**:
      ```sql
      CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE #TempTicketIDs (
        DetailID INT
      )
      ```
    end note
    
    :Parse Comma-Separated IDs;
    note right
      **String Split Logic**:
      ```sql
      -- MySQL 8.0+
      INSERT INTO #TempTicketIDs (DetailID)
      SELECT CAST(value AS UNSIGNED) as DetailID
      FROM JSON_TABLE(
        CONCAT('["', 
          REPLACE(@ip_MMDetailsIDList, ',', '","'), 
        '"]'),
        '$[*]' COLUMNS(value VARCHAR(50) PATH '$')
      ) AS jt
      WHERE value REGEXP '^[0-9]+$'
      
      -- Alternative for older MySQL
      -- Use FIND_IN_SET or custom split function
      ```
      
      **Example**:
      Input: "12345,67890,11111"
      Result: 3 rows in #TempTicketIDs
    end note
  endif
}

partition "Update Ticket Status" {
  if (Has Ticket IDs?) then (yes)
    :Mark Tickets as Processed;
    note right
      **Update Fraud Tickets**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CTSMatchMonitorDetail
      SET 
        IsProcessed = 1,
        ProcessedDate = NOW(),
        IsFraud = 1,
        FraudDetectedDate = NOW()
      WHERE ID IN (SELECT DetailID FROM #TempTicketIDs)
        AND MatchID = @ip_MatchID
        AND IsProcessed = 0  -- Only update unprocessed
      ```
      
      **Fields Updated**:
      - IsProcessed = 1 (mark as done)
      - ProcessedDate (timestamp)
      - IsFraud = 1 (confirmed fraud)
      - FraudDetectedDate (detection time)
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Remove from processing queue
      - Track fraud tickets
      - Audit trail
      - Prevent reprocessing
    end note
    
    :Check Affected Rows;
    note right
      **Validation**:
      ```sql
      SELECT @AffectedRows = ROW_COUNT()
      ```
      
      **Log if mismatch**:
      - Expected: Count of IDs in list
      - Actual: @AffectedRows
      - Could indicate:
        * Already processed tickets
        * Invalid ticket IDs
        * MatchID mismatch
    end note
  endif
}

partition "Update Match Status" {
  :Check All Tickets Processed;
  note right
    **Verify Match Completion**:
    ```sql
    SELECT @UnprocessedCount = COUNT(*)
    FROM CTSMatchMonitorDetail
    WHERE MatchID = @ip_MatchID
      AND (IsProcessed = 0 OR IsProcessed IS NULL)
    ```
    
    **If @UnprocessedCount = 0**:
    - All tickets processed
    - Match can be marked complete
    
    **If @UnprocessedCount > 0**:
    - Some tickets still pending
    - Keep match in queue
    - Will be reprocessed
  end note
  
  if (@UnprocessedCount = 0?) then (yes)
    :Mark Match as Completed;
    note right
      **Complete Match**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CTSMatchMonitor
      SET 
        IsCompleted = 1,
        IsProcessing = 0,
        CompletedDate = NOW(),
        ProcessEndTime = NOW(),
        TotalFraudTickets = (
          SELECT COUNT(*)
          FROM CTSMatchMonitorDetail
          WHERE MatchID = @ip_MatchID
            AND IsFraud = 1
        )
      WHERE MatchID = @ip_MatchID
      ```
      
      **Fields Updated**:
      - IsCompleted = 1 (fully done)
      - IsProcessing = 0 (unlock)
      - CompletedDate (finish timestamp)
      - ProcessEndTime (duration tracking)
      - TotalFraudTickets (summary count)
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Remove from queue permanently
      - Unlock for reporting
      - Complete audit trail
      - Performance metrics
    end note
  else (no)
    :Keep Match in Queue;
    note right
      **Partial Completion**:
      ```sql
      UPDATE CTSMatchMonitor
      SET 
        IsProcessing = 0,
        LastPartialProcessDate = NOW()
      WHERE MatchID = @ip_MatchID
      ```
      
      **Reason**:
      - Some tickets not yet flagged
      - Needs reprocessing
      - Detection rules evolving
      - Data still being collected
      
      **Next Run**:
      - Will pick this match again
      - Process remaining tickets
      - Eventually mark complete
    end note
  endif
}

partition "Cleanup" {
  :Drop Temp Tables;
  note right
    **Cleanup**:
    ```sql
    DROP TEMPORARY TABLE IF EXISTS #TempTicketIDs
    ```
    
    **Memory Management**:
    - Free temp table memory
    - Clean session resources
  end note
}

:Complete;

note right
  **Key Characteristics**:
  
  **Atomic Operation**:
  - All updates in one transaction
  - Rollback on error
  - Consistency guaranteed
  
  **Idempotent**:
  - Can be called multiple times
  - Already processed tickets skipped
  - No side effects on re-run
  
  **Queue Management**:
  - Removes completed matches
  - Keeps partial matches in queue
  - FIFO order maintained
  
  **Performance**:
  - Indexed on MatchID, IsProcessed
  - Bulk update for tickets
  - Single match update
  - Fast execution
  
  **Error Handling**:
  - Invalid MatchID: No rows affected
  - Invalid ticket IDs: Logged
  - Constraint violations: Rollback
  - Timeout: Automatic retry
  
  **Related Operations**:
  - Called after classification complete
  - Updates detection results
  - Maintains processing queue
  - Enables reporting
end note

stop

@enduml

